triples.evidence: To compute the coefficient b3 from the Fourier series of some known function - say f of t, we take the sine function, sine of 2 pi times 3 t, which is one of our orthonormal basis functions, and we compute its inner product with f of t. That means we integrate the product of f of t and sine of 2 pi times 3 t over the interval from 0 to 1.

concepts.term: To compute b n, you use the sine of 2 pi n t as your basis function, multiply it by f of t, and integrate from 0 to 1
